

Carlos P&lt;U+00E9&gt;rez Su&lt;U+00E1&gt;rez (born July 14, 1994 in Guadalajara, Jalisco, Mexico) is a Mexican professional boxer in the Light Welterweight division.1 Carlos is promoted by current WBC Champion, Mexican Sa&lt;U+00FA&gt;l &lt;U+00C1&gt;lvarez' company Canelo Promotions.2
Amateur career
During his amateur career he had seventeen fights, going 16-1.3
Professional career
In December 2010, P&lt;U+00E9&gt;rez beat the veteran Ivan Rodriguez at the Arena Jalisco in Guadalajara, Jalisco, Mexico.4
In his next fight Carlos lost against the veteran Cesar Figueroa, on the undercard Sa&lt;U+00FA&gt;l &lt;U+00C1&gt;lvarez vs. Ryan Rhodes.5
